</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/upentagarnmanastorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentagarn Manastorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/8/02 1:12:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=169>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: resist cap</span><hr size=1> I did not read the entire 9 pages but got the general premise.<br>
<br>
Compromise that is very easy to implement.  Make more spells like Ice Spear of the Solist.<br>
<br>
1200 damage/300mana but has a recast delay.  As every sorcerer know ice spear rocks and makes a 60 wizard considerably more valuable to a group.<br>
<br>
Then make spells like this with lower damge/lower mana across all levels.  You have your group nukes, you have fast burn nukes, you have AE's, rains, PB AE's (they change jylls, they die) and I think life would be better.<br>
<br>
You can increase the groupablity of a wizard across all levels, without making him burning destruction machine.  The concept of ice spear was wonderful.  I dont know about hard core numbers but this would seem logical.  You want to burn a mob into the ground you pay for it, but for contributing damage to a group this would be ideal.  This makes wizards more groupable.<br>
<br>
In my opinon, we should not match rogues in damage over time.  That is all they do besides pick a lock and sneak.  The difference is in the ease of twinkability in this class vice the relative untwinkability of a wizard.  (Wouldn't you love to hook up a newbie wizard with a vermillion orb)  Ports get us groups, not by desireability for evacs but for making groups.  I dont walk into velks and just get picked up, but if I pick up group members I usually get into groups.<br>
<br>
Rogues can not AE.  Dont know how you AE but my AE exp is just incredible.  They would have to be primal stupid twinked rogues in ideal circumstances to make as much exp as I do AE, and that includes the occasional greedy wipeout.<br>
<br>
I will admit getting to 60 totally sucks but it does make it that much more worth it.  I am baised due to being 60, but I am proud that I earned it.  Very few 60 twink wizards.  Keeping it tough adds value to being 60.<br>
<br>
The mob issue, make some like gore.  Lure resist AE slow.  This will force people to use some more magic user types in battles.  As far as ToV, I rack in more damage than everyone (rogue, DS stacked MT, monk), I dont enrage sucide, I can avoid AE's.<br>
<br>
For pre-60 I feel for you.  Long road ahead but it is worth it until then.  I personally dont want to see a bunch of twink wizards and when I usually see a lower level wizard I know it is usually not a twink (unless some guild made a TL slave)<br>
