<br>
This is mainly in response to MiteBe, who listed 12 'roles' for characters in a 6 person group.  His list, to me, epitomizes what is wrong with the PERCEPTIONS of the wizard class, even by other wizards.<br>
<br>
He lists three roles that wizards are generally put into:<br>
Snarer<br>
Evacer<br>
Damage Dealer<br>
<br>
Wizards certainly can and do serve in all three of those roles, and sometimes they even do all three at once.<br>
<br>
And a high-level wizard with his epic and a Staff of Temperate Flux can be a very good puller.  Not as good as an FDer, but at least as good as any non-FD puller.<br>
<br>
But the biggest role that a wizard can and should play in a 6 person group is this:  &quot;the weapon of last resort.&quot;  We are the ones, MUCH more than any other class, even paladins with LoH, who can save a party's collective asses, when things start to go wrong.  This can be as simple as taking aggro from an enchanter having trouble with the mob(s) that had a nearby caster mob buff their MR just before being pulled, or similarly rescuing the cleric who has gotten aggro.  It can even apply to more complex situations such as just too many little mobs around for the enchanter to keep mezzed w/o going oom, just nuke 1-2 down to a crisp and problem solved.  Sure, you may be medding the rest of the fight and into the next one to recover your mana, but you just enabled the group to do something they could not have done w/o you, even a much higher sustained damage dealer can not do what you just did.<br>
<br>
This relates to what I keep trying bring home to my fellow wizards.  Wizards are about FOCUSED damage.  Timing is everything.  When to nuke light and keep a full mana pull for when it is needed.  When it is needed, how to burn quickly, non-stop to get the job done.  This is one reason why I regard the Staff of Temperate Flux and its proper use to be sign of a really good wizard.  Not the epic.  Even mages, our closest competitors, can not hold a candle to wizards in this kind of situation.  Why?  Its not because they are less efficient, they are.  And its not because they get resisted more, they do.  But the BIG thing is that they are SLOW!  And they do not have the Staff 0f Temperate Flux to let them skip most of the 2.25 sec recast delay.   Many mages have trouble squeezing off more than one nuke in a fight, not because they would run out of mana, but because by the time they wait for tanks to get aggro and then land their first nuke, the fight is OVER before the second nuke can get there.<br>
<br>
That fast damage gives wizards a certain flexibility and enormous power.  If you are not using that power, then you really are not being a wizard.<br>
<br>
OTOH, I do agree completely that ALL casters have been getting the shaft and the disparity keeps growing with every expansion.  Luclin was supposed to be the expansion for casters.  I must admit that it seems that Verant got that PARTLY right.  The gulf between melees and casters did grow with Luclin, in my opinion.  But the amount by which it grew is less than it was for Kunark or Velious.<br>
<br>
That does need to be addressed, but I do not see that as a wizard issue, I see it as an issue for all casters. <p>Yugy of the Nexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/9/02 11:38:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=175>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> Hehe.. in my experience wizards can split mobs by really dying instead of just faking it.<br>
